Strongest, Strengthening, Average, Weakening, Weakest. A buy or sell signal with a "strongest" direction means the signal is becoming stronger. A Hold signal direction indicates where the signal is heading (towards a buy or sell): Bullish, Rising, Steady, Falling, Bearish.

desc: 5-Year Price Change: The difference between the current price, and the settlement price from 5-Years ago.

name: 5Y %Change
desc: 5-Year Percent Change: The difference between the current price and the settlement price from 5 years ago expressed as a percentage.

name: 5Y Nbr Highs
desc: The number of times the price has reached a new high over the last 5 years.

name: 5Y % From High
desc: The percent difference from the current price to the 5-year high.

name: 5Y Nbr Lows
desc: The number of times the price has reached a new low over the last 5 years.

name: 5Y % From Low
desc: The percent difference from the current price to the 5-year low.

name: 5-Year Price Range %Change
desc: The current price range over a 5-year period, expressed as a percent. ((last price - 5Y low) / (5Y high - 5Y low)) * 100.0

name: 10Y High
desc: The highest price over the last 10 years.

name: 10Y High Date

name: 10Y Low

name: 10Y Nbr Lows

name: 10Y % From Low

name: 10-Year Price Range %Change

name: All-Time Low Date

desc: The percent difference between the current price and the settlement price from the earliest date.

name: All-Time Nbr Highs

name: All-Time % From High

name: All-Time Nbr Lows

name: All-Time % From Low

name: Market Capitalization, $K
desc: The total equity market value of the company: the shares outstanding times the stock price (in thousands of dollars).

name: Enterprise Value, $K
desc: Enterprise Value is the measure of a company’s total value. It is computed by the sum of the current Market Capitalization, Short Term Debt, Long Term Debt, Minority Interests and Preferred Stock minus Cash & Equivalents.

name: Shares Outstanding, K
desc: Common shares that have been authorized, issued, and purchased by investors.

name: Annual Sales
desc: The annual sales.

name: Annual Net Income
desc: The annual net income.

name: Last Quarter Sales
desc: The last quarter sales.

name: Last Quarter Net Income
desc: The last quarter net income.

name: 60-Month Beta
desc: Coefficient that measures the volatility of a stock's returns relative to the market (S&P 500), based on a 60-month historical regression of the return on the stock onto the return on the S&P 500.

name: % Insider Shareholders
desc: The percent of ownership held by the company's executives, board of directors, and other senior officials.

name: % Institutional Shareholders
desc: The percent of ownership held by large financial institutions or organizations.

name: Float, K
desc: The regular shares a company has issued that are available to trade (shares outstanding - restricted stock).

name: % Float
desc: The percentage of regular shares a company has issued that are available to trade (float / shares outstanding * 100).

name: Five-Year Revenue Growth
desc: The revenue growth percent over a 5-Year period. Growth is based on comparing the value from 5-years ago against the present value, reflected as a percentage.

name: EBIT(a)
desc: EBIT, or Earnings before interest and taxes, is a measure of a firm's profit that excludes interest and income tax expenses. Expressed in millions of dollars, EBIT = Revenue - Operating expenses + Non-operating income.

name: EBITDA(a)
desc: EBITDA is net income (earnings) with interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization added back, expressed in millions of dollars.

name: Most Recent Earnings
desc: Earnings per share, or the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock.

name: Last Earnings Date
desc: The last reported Earnings Date.

name: Latest Earnings Date
desc: The next reported earnings date, or the latest earnings date as reported by the company (if no future date has been released).

name: Report Released
desc: The date on which the earnings report is released.

name: Earnings Per Share ttm
desc: Earnings per share, or the portion of a company's profit allocated to each outstanding share of common stock, for the last trailing twelve months.

name: EPS Growth vs. Prev Quarter
desc: The earnings per share growth over the previous quarter.

name: EPS Growth vs. Prev Year
desc: The earnings per share growth from the most recent EPS compared to the quarterly EPS from 4 quarters before.

name: 5-Year Earnings Growth
desc: The earnings growth percent over a 5-Year period.

name: Dividend Rate
desc: The trailing annual dividend amount paid.

name: Dividend Yield
desc: Annual dividend yield is trailing annual dividend amount divided by the latest closing price.

name: Most Recent Dividend
desc: The last dividend paid.

name: Last Dividend Date
desc: The ex-dividend date on which the most recent dividend was paid.

name: Dividend Date
desc: The next ex-dividend date, or the latest ex-dividend date if no future date has been released.

name: Dividend Payable Date
desc: The next dividend payable date, or the latest dividend payable date if no future date has been released.

name: Dividend Payout Ratio
desc: Dividend payout ratio is the % of net income paid to stockholders in dividends.

name: 5-Year Dividends Growth
desc: The dividends growth percent over a 5-Year period.

name: Split
desc: The share split recorded on the last split date.

name: Split Date
desc: The date on which a share split last occurred.

name: Price/Earnings ttm
desc: The closing price divided by the earnings-per-share based on the last trailing twelve months (TTM) of earnings.

name: Price/Earnings Forward
desc: The projected price to earnings per share valuation.

name: Price/Earnings to Growth
desc: The price/earnings growth ratio.

name: Return-on-Equity %
desc: For the recent quarter (after taxes): earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items) divided by the Most Recent Quarter Common Stock Equity.

name: Return-on-Assets %
desc: For the recent quarter (before taxes): earnings from total operations (not including extraordinary items) divided by the Most Recent Quarter Assets.

name: Profit Margin %
desc: For the recent year, a measure of profitability, equal to annual net income / revenues over the selected period * 100.

name: Debt/Equity
desc: The debt/equity ratio for the latest quarter. Debt/Equity is a financial health ratio that adds long-term debt to current liabilities, then divides by the last fiscal year net equity per share of common stock.

name: Price/Sales
desc: Latest closing price of the stock divided by the last twelve months revenue/sales per share.

name: Price/Cash Flow
desc: Latest closing price of the stock divided by the last twelve months revenue/cash flow per share.

name: Price/Book
desc: A financial ratio used to compare a company's current market price to its book value.

name: Book Value/Share
desc: The per share value of a company based on its equity available to common shareholders for the trailing 12 months.

name: Interest Coverage
desc: A measure of a company's ability to honor its interest payments.  (Annual Pre-Tax Income + Annual Interest Expense) / Annual Interest Expense

name: Analyst Rating
desc: The current average Analyst Rating, where Strong Buy = 5, Moderate Buy = 4, Hold = 3, Moderate Sell = 2, Strong Sell = 1.

name: Nbr of Analysts
desc: The number of analysts submitting ratings for the current period.

name: Avg Earnings Estimate
desc: The average analysts' estimate for earnings for the current quarter.

name: Estimated Earnings
desc: Estimated quarterly earnings from the last reported quarter, as reported by analysts.

name: High Target Price Estimate
desc: The 12-Month High Target Price from analysts who provided ratings

name: Mean Target Price Estimate
desc: The 12-Month Mean Target Price from analysts who provided ratings

name: Low Target Price Estimate
desc: The 12-Month Low Target Price from analysts who provided ratings

name: Estimated Earnings 1-Qtr Ago
desc: Estimated quarterly earnings 1-quarter ago as reported by analysts.

name: Estimated Earnings 2-Qtrs Ago
desc: Estimated quarterly earnings 2-quarters ago as reported by analysts.

name: Estimated Earnings 3-Qtrs Ago
desc: Estimated quarterly earnings 3-quarters ago, as reported by analysts.

name: Reported Earnings
desc: Last reported quarterly earnings, based on GAAP income from continuing operations.

name: Reported Earnings 1-Qtr Ago
desc: The reported quarterly earnings from 1-quarter ago, based on GAAP income from continuing operations.

name: Reported Earnings 2-Qtrs Ago
desc: The reported quarterly earnings from 2-quarters ago, based on GAAP income from continuing operations.

name: Reported Earnings 3-Qtrs Ago

desc: The difference between the reported and estimated earnings from 1-quarter ago.

name: Earnings Difference 2-Qtrs Ago

name: Earnings Difference 3-Qtrs Ago

desc: The ATM average implied volatility relative to the highest and lowest values over the past 1-year. If IV Rank is 100% this means the IV is at its highest level over the past 1-year.

name: 6-Month Implied Volatility Rank

name: Premium
desc: The price of the options contract. (Option Last Price * Option Volume)

name: Option Type
desc: Put or Call. A Call option gives you the right to buy a stock and a Put option gives you the right to sell a stock.

name: Expiration Date
desc: The option expiration date.

name: Expiration Type
desc: The type of option expiration: monthly or weekly.

name: Days Till Expiration
desc: The number of days until the option expires.

name: Trade Time
desc: Time of last trade for the options contract.

name: Expires Before Earnings
desc: Yes/No to indicate whether the option expires before the next earnings date.

name: Options are Restricted
desc: A non-standard or 'restricted option' is typically created after spin-offs or mergers, and is not tradable.

name: Net Debit
desc: Net Debit (Break Even) = stock price - bid

name: Options Potential Return
desc: The potential return% for the covered call strategy. ((Options Strike + Bid + Dividend - Stock Price) / (Stock Price - Bid))

name: Options Potential Return Annual
desc: The potential annual return% for the covered call strategy. (((Options Strike + Bid + Dividend - Stock Price) / (Stock Price - Bid))) * (365 /DTE)

name: Options Flat
desc: If Stock Last Price > Strike Price then ((Options Strike + Bid + Dividends - Stock Price) / (Stock Price - Bid)) - else when Stock Last Price <= Strike Price then (Bid / (Stock Price + Dividends - Bid)) * 100.0

name: Options Flat Annual
desc: The potential annual return% (if flat) for the covered call strategy. ((Bid + Dividend) / (Stock Price - Bid))) * (365 /DTE)

name: Static Return%
desc: Static Return or Downside Protection, assuming the options are not assigned or called away. (Bid + Dividend) / Stock Price

name: Ann Static Return%
desc: Static Return or Downside Protection annualized return, assuming the options are not assigned or called away. Calculated as Static Return * (365 / DTE)

name: Moneyness
desc: Relative position of the underlying price to the strike price. (Underlying Price) - (Strike Price of Option)

name: Theoretical Edge
desc: The theoretical edge reflects the change in the option price if the current strike IV normalized to the 30 day HV in terms of dollar vega change. $Vega = 30-Day Historical Volatility minus strike Implied Volatility multiplied by Vega.

name: Distance from Strike
desc: The difference ($) between the underlying asset's last price and the strike price (Stock Price - Options Strike)

name: Implied Volatility
desc: Implied Volatility is the estimated volatility of the option strike over the period of the option.

name: Volatility %Change
desc: The option's strike percent change in implied volatility from the previous session.

name: BE (Bid)
desc: Strike + Bid for calls and Strike - Bid for puts

name: BE (Mid)
desc: Strike + Midpoint for calls and Strike - Midpoint for puts

name: BE (Ask)
desc: Strike + Ask for calls and Strike - Ask for puts

name: BE (Last)
desc: Strike + Last for calls and Strike - Last for puts

name: %BE (Bid)
desc: The percentage by which the stock price has to move to reach Breakeven (Uncovered). ((Strike + Bid - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for calls and ((Strike - Bid - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for puts

name: %BE (Mid)
desc: The percentage by which the stock price has to move to reach Breakeven (Uncovered). ((Strike + Midpoint - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for calls and ((Strike - Midpoint - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for puts

name: %BE (Ask)
desc: The percentage by which the stock price has to move to reach Breakeven (Uncovered). ((Strike + Ask - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for calls and ((Strike - Ask - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for puts

name: %BE (Last)
desc: The percentage by which the stock price has to move to reach Breakeven (Uncovered). ((Strike + Last - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for calls and ((Strike - Last - Stock Price) / Stock Price) * 100.0 for puts

name: Theoretical
desc: The hypothetical or theoretical value of the option, calculated by the binomial options model.

name: Delta
desc: Measures the sensitivity of an option's theoretical value to a change in the price of the underlying asset.

name: Gamma
desc: Measures the rate of change in the delta for each one-point increase in the underlying asset.

name: Theta
desc: A measure of the time decay of an option, the dollar amount that an option will lose each day due to the passage of time.

name: Vega
desc: Measures the sensitivity of the price of an option to changes in volatility.

name: Rho
desc: The rate at which the price of a derivative changes relative to a change in the risk-free rate of interest.

name: Net Delta / Net Theta
desc: Delta to theta ratio (Delta / Theta)

name: Net Theta / Net Gamma
desc: Theta to gamma ratio (Theta / Gamma)

name: Net Theta / Net Vega
desc: Theta to vega ratio (Theta / Vega)

name: ITM Probability
desc: For a call option, the probability that the underlying price is above the option's strike price at expiration. For a put option, the probability that the underlying price is below the option's strike price at expiration.

name: OTM Probability
desc: For a call option, the probability that the underlying price is below the option's strike price at expiration. For a put option, the probability that the underlying price is above the option's strike price at expiration.

name: Bid% of Stock
desc: Options Bid / Stock Price (expressed as a percentage)

name: Ask% of Stock
desc: Options Ask / Stock Price (expressed as a percentage)

name: MidPoint% of Stock
desc: Options MidPoint / Stock Price (expressed as a percentage)

name: Last% of Stock
desc: Options Last / Stock Price (expressed as a percentage)

name: Time Premium Bid
desc: The extrinsic value (Bid - Intrinsic Value) of the option if ITM, else if OTM then Bid price.

name: %Time Premium Bid
desc: The amount by which an option's price exceeds its intrinsic value if ITM ((Bid - Intrinsic Value) / Stock Price), else if OTM then (Bid / Stock Price)

name: %Time Premium Bid Annual Return
desc: %Time Premium Annual Return = %TP * 365 / DTE

name: Time Premium Ask
desc: The extrinsic value (Ask - Intrinsic Value) of the option if ITM, else if OTM then Ask price.

name: %Time Premium Ask
desc: The amount by which an option's price exceeds its intrinsic value if ITM ((Ask - Intrinsic Value) / Stock Price), else if OTM then (Ask / Stock Price)

name: %Time Premium Ask Annual Return
desc: %Time Premium Ask Annual Return = %TP Ask * 365 / DTE

name: Time Premium Mid
desc: The extrinsic value (Mid - Intrinsic Value) of the option if ITM, else if OTM then Mid price.

name: %Time Premium Midpoint
desc: The amount by which an option's price exceeds its intrinsic value if ITM ((Mid - Intrinsic Value) / Stock Price), else if OTM then (Mid / Stock Price)

name: %Time Premium Midpoint Annual Return
desc: %Time Premium Midpoint Annual Return = %TP Midpoint * 365 / DTE

name: Time Premium Last
desc: The extrinsic value (Last - Intrinsic Value) of the option if ITM, else if OTM then Last price.

name: %Time Premium Last
desc: The amount by which an option's price exceeds its intrinsic value if ITM ((Bid - Intrinsic Value) / Stock Price), else if OTM then (Bid / Stock Price)

name: %Time Premium Last Annual Return
desc: %Time Premium Last Annual Return = %TP Last * 365 / DTE

name: Yield to Strike%
desc: Yield to Strike % = (Bid Price) / Strike Price

name: Ann Yield to Strike%
desc: The potential annual return% for the strategy. Yield to Strike Annual Return = (Bid Price) / Strike Price × (365 days per year/DTE)

name: Static Return%
desc: Static Return or Downside Protection, assuming the options are not assigned or called away. (Bid + Dividend) / Stock Price

name: Ann Static Return%
desc: Static Return or Downside Protection annualized return, assuming the options are not assigned or called away. Calculated as Static Return * (365 / DTE)

name: Strike within 1 Standard Deviation
desc: Symbols whose strike price is between 1 Standard Deviation Support and 1 Standard Deviation Resistance.

name: Strike within 2 Standard Deviations
desc: Symbols whose strike price is between 2 Standard Deviations Support and 2 Standard Deviations Resistance.

name: Strike within 3 Standard Deviation
desc: Symbols whose strike price is between 3 Standard Deviations Support and 3 Standard Deviations Resistance.

name: Option Premium
desc: The price of the options trade (premium = option spot x volume x 100 underlying shares).

name: Option Trade Size
desc: The option trade volume.

name: ETF Full Name
desc: The full name identified by the Fund Family.

name: Fund Family
desc: A company offering many ETFs or mutual funds, for various objectives.

name: Asset Class
desc: The type of assets contained in the ETF.

name: Leverage
desc: The factor by which an ETF moves in correlation to the underlying Index.

name: Assets Under Management
desc: Assets Under Management (AUM) is the total market value of all financial assets managed by the ETF or Fund.

name: Net Asset Value
desc: Net Asset Value (NAV) is the per share price of the fund (total net assets / number of shares outstanding, minus fees & expenses.)

name: Management Fee
desc: An expense ratio that measures what it costs the investment company to manage the ETF.

name: Alpha
desc: A measurement of how an ETF is performing in relation to its benchmark index.

name: Contract Name
desc: A shortened version of the symbol name.

name: Expiration Date
desc: The expiration date for a futures contract.

name: Days Till Expiration
desc: The number of days until the futures contract expires.

name: First Notice Date
desc: The first notice date for a futures contract, after which time the owner of the contract can take physical delivery of the underlying asset.

name: Days Till First Notice
desc: The number of days until the futures contract first notice, after which time the owner of the contract can take physical delivery of the underlying asset

name: Point Value
desc: A measure of one basis point change in the futures price

name: Margin
desc: The approximate amount of money that you must deposit and keep on hand with your broker when you open a futures position.

name: Open Interest
desc: The total number of open contracts for the previous day that have been traded but not yet liquidated via offsetting trades.

name: Quantity
desc: The quantity open on the transaction.

name: Action
desc: Initial transaction position, either Buy or Sell.

name: Entry Date
desc: The transaction entry date.

name: Entry Price
desc: The price at which the initial transaction was entered at.

name: Exit Date
desc: The date on which the transaction was closed.

name: Exit Price
desc: The price at which the transaction was closed.

name: Commission
desc: The total fees associated with the transaction.

name: Stock Value
desc: The current market value (Last Price if no Exit Price, or Entry Price for a Sell transaction) * Quantity.

name: Daily Return
desc: The daily profit or loss. This field is blank if trade is liquidated before today.

name: Return
desc: The total profit or loss.

name: Total Price Change
desc: The total dollar change (the difference between the Exit Price (or Last Price, if no Exit Price) and the Entry Price).

name: Total Percent Change
desc: The total percent change.
